name: The weight of society
description: It doesn't matter what kind of person you are. You live in society. It doesn't matter if you are sociable, antisocial, cheerful, serious, lonely... you live in society. We all have to learn to bear that weight and swim in those waters, whether we like it or not. So, when you see a person who doesn't fit in, think about everything that comes with living in society, the rules, what is not established, what is expected of everyone... do you think that everyone can integrate equally well?
